pros:
The impact that you can have given the voice and funding of the foundation - against a mission statement that all lives have equal value - working here feeds my soul (until you bump up against politics and processes);
Great benefits and compensation package;
CEO is inspirational

cons:
Too many politics, too much process - too much jumping from what already works to what is "new and shiny";
Highly dependent on external management consultants for technical strategy development (huh? what's that about? what about all those great technical people you have on staff?);
Poor leadership/management skills at mid-level
